basic.floral_language:
Mixed color mini-rose
Mixed color mini-rose Floriography: enthusiasm, brave and independent
Mixed color mini-rose is a rose family, was cultivated in the flower kingdom of the Netherlands.
Mixed color mini-rose has various colors, and its fragrance is quietly elegant. Inherited the fine quality of the rose family, but with a stature of cabinet and chic, Mixed color mini-rose was popular in Europe market at the beginning of the launch, and has become the new favorite of household and desktop decoration. 
Mixed color mini-rose likes the sun light, flowering for 2-3 weeks at a time. Bud sprouts after pruning, and under normal circumstances Mixed color mini-rose can be perpetual.
basic.blooming: Blooms once every February-March months, viewing period 2-3 weeks
basic.color: Flower color a mixture of red and yellow

maintenance.soil: Peat or soil with specific nutrients
maintenance.sunlight: Likes sunshine, put in sunny places, avoid strong sunlight in summer at noon
maintenance.watering: Water thoroughly when soil is dry, avoid saturated water
maintenance.fertilization: Dilute fertilizers following instructions, apply 2-3 times monthly
maintenance.pruning: Remove old, diseased and dead leaves timely, after flowering remove the upper part staring from 5 cm above soil surface, leaving 2-3 leaves
